item.title: #520 Output needed
item.dc:creator: @qauters qauters
item.description:
@qauters wrote:

[quote=“the bank, post:20, topic:239646”][quote author=nueb35 link=topic=315942.msg2510602#msg2510602 date=1225248112]
but team is not an icon, team is just for the cape correct? there should be another int they are probably hooked the same, and just because others have the same output does not make it right. be the difference and find a way to fix it.
[/quote]Actually, you are wrong, and he is right.[/quote]
Didn’t quite understand you here.

Team is a value indicating the team you are on (like Miss Silabsoft said). It’s used to determine it should paint a blue dot or not:

if (myPlayer.team != 0 && player.team != 0 &&  myPlayer.team == player.team)
   sameTeam = true;

The pk head icon and the prayer head icon are just indexes in the icon arrays.

if (player.pkHeadIcon != -1 || player.prayerHeadIcon != -1) {
   npcScreenPos(-80, 15 + entity.height, entity);
   if (spriteDrawX > -1) {
      if (player.pkHeadIcon != -1) {
         headIcons_PK[player.pkHeadIcon].drawSprite((-12 + i_74_ + Class74_Sub12_Sub16_Sub1.spriteDrawX), (-i_79_ + Class74_Sub7_Sub26.spriteDrawY + i_75_));
         i_79_ += 25;
      }
      if (player.prayerHeadIcon != -1) {
         headIcons_Prayer[player.prayerHeadIcon].drawSprite((-12 + Class74_Sub12_Sub16_Sub1.spriteDrawX + i_74_), Class74_Sub7_Sub26.spriteDrawY + i_75_ + -i_79_);
         i_79_ += 25;
      }
   }
}

The current fields are these:

Class Player: wk
   Field Team: wk.ob
   Field PKHeadIcon: wk.dc
   Field PrayerHeadIcon: wk.Xb
